{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":150229,"duration_api_ms":145604,"num_turns":2,"result":"## core_business_v2/ingestion Module Overview\n\n### What It Does\nAn **async event-driven entity ingestion pipeline** — receives entity events (hosts, user-host bindings) via REST, processes them through a 4-stage state machine (label → evaluate → enforce), with Redis-based distributed locking, fingerprint deduplication, and request interruption support.\n\n---\n\n### REST Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| **POST** | `/api/v1/ingestion/events` | Main entry — publishes to Redis stream, waits 60s for async result |\n| **GET** | `/api/v1/ingestion/health-check` | Returns \"OK\" |\n| **POST** | `/api/v1/entities/query` | Query failed entities with filters + pagination |\n| **GET** | `/api/v1/entities/{id}` | Get entity by ID |\n| **GET** | `/api/v1/entities/{id}/display-status` | Display-friendly state mapping |\n| **POST** | `/api/v1/policy/apply-existing-entities` | Mark all entities for policy reprocessing |\n| **POST** | `/api/v1/fingerprint/calculate` | Calculate fingerprint hash for given entity |\n\n---\n\n### Request Processing Flow\n\n```\nPOST /api/v1/ingestion/events\n        │\n        ▼\nIngestionController — generates requestId, registers CompletableFuture callback, publishes to Redis stream\n        │\n        ▼\nIngestionInternalConsumer (16 consumers) — reads from stream, calls IngestionOrchestrator\n        │\n        ▼\nIngestionOrchestrator — 3-way branch:\n  ├─ Cache HIT → CachedExistingEntityHandler\n  ├─ Cache MISS + lock acquired → DB lookup → NewEntityHandler or DbExistingEntityHandler\n  └─ Cache MISS + lock failed → requeue with exponential backoff (2-32s, max 5 retries)\n        │\n        ▼\nFingerprintHandlerRegistry — dispatches on (sameFingerprint, lockAcquired):\n  ├─ SAME + LOCK → return entity as-is (idempotent)\n  ├─ SAME + NO_LOCK → poll DB 60s waiting for completion\n  ├─ DIFF + LOCK → reset to PENDING, restart state machine\n  └─ DIFF + NO_LOCK → interrupt running SM, acquire lock, reset & restart\n        │\n        ▼\nEntityStateMachine.start() — loops through stages:\n  PENDING → LabelService.label()\n  LABELED → PolicyService.evaluate()\n  EVALUATED → EnforcementService.enforce()\n  ENFORCED (terminal)\n  Each stage: 3 retries with backoff, DB persist on transition\n        │\n        ▼\nCallback completes → REST response returned to caller\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Classes & Responsibilities\n\n**Controllers:** `IngestionController`, `EntityController`, `PolicyController`, `FingerprintController`\n\n**Consumer Layer:**\n- **IngestionInternalConsumer** — Redis stream consumer (16 instances), ACK-based, drives the pipeline\n- **IngestionExternalConsumer** — Ingests from external stream (8 instances), validates, republishes internally\n- **IngestionOrchestrator** — Cache/lock decision tree, routes to appropriate handler\n\n**Handlers (fingerprint-based dispatch):**\n- **NewEntityHandler** — Creates entity, builds fingerprint, acquires PROCESS_LOCK, starts SM\n- **CachedExistingEntityHandler / DbExistingEntityHandler** — Fingerprint comparison → FingerprintHandlerRegistry\n- **DeviceTypeChangedHandler** — Handles HOST → USER_HOST_BINDING promotion\n- **SameAttributes[With/Without]LockHandler**, **DifferentAttributes[With/Without]LockHandler** — 4 concrete strategies\n\n**State Machine:**\n- **EntityStateMachine** — Stage loop with retry, failpoint injection, metrics\n- **EntityStageTransactionRunner** — Wraps each stage call in a transaction\n\n**Services:**\n- **LabelService** — Calls classification rule engine\n- **PolicyService** — Policy evaluation (currently mock)\n- **EnforcementService** — Enforcement action (currently mock)\n- **EntityServiceImpl** — CRUD, batch operations, reprocess marking\n- **FingerprintServiceImpl** — Attribute hash computation\n\n**Infrastructure:**\n- **IngestionCallbackRegistry** — requestId → CompletableFuture mapping (bridges async consumer back to REST)\n- **EntityCache** — Redis-based entity ID cache\n- **DistributedLock** — Redis CREATE_LOCK and PROCESS_LOCK\n\n**Jobs:**\n- **PolicyReprocessJob** — Scans entities marked INIT, re-runs SM (every 30s + event-driven)\n- **StuckEntityRecoveryJob** — Recovers entities stuck >80s in non-terminal state\n\n---\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Callback Registry** — Decouples synchronous REST from async stream processing\n2. **Distributed Locking** — Redis-based CREATE_LOCK / PROCESS_LOCK with TTL\n3. **Fingerprint Deduplication** — Attribute hash comparison to skip redundant processing\n4. **Request Interruption** — Newer requests interrupt stale in-flight processing\n5. **State Machine with Retry** — 4-stage pipeline, 3 retries per stage, exponential backoff\n6. **Handler Registry** — Enum-based dispatch on `(sameFingerprint, lockAcquired)` → 4 strategies","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"cf2666c6-de68-4205-a43a-31ce14335eb0","total_cost_usd":0.5152065,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22095,"cache_read_input_tokens":36936,"output_tokens":1683,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":22095,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6[1m]":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":1683,"cacheReadInputTokens":36936,"cacheCreationInputTokens":22095,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.19865675,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":84,"outputTokens":11854,"cacheReadInputTokens":1054520,"cacheCreationInputTokens":121395,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.3165497500000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"3d0ef69b-6400-48f3-ae95-61ffa3841875"}
